  "notes": "Sardinian. THE most conservative Romance language. Primary archaic features: (1) Velars /k, ɡ/ preserved before front vowels (kentu 'hundred', not *centu). (2) 5-vowel system (no ɛ/e or ɔ/o split). (3) No diphthongisation of Latin ĕ, ŏ. (4) Retroflex consonants [ɖː] from Latin -LL-. (5) Article from IPSE (su/sa) not ILLE. Sardinian forms its OWN primary branch of Romance, diverging before Italo-, Gallo-, Ibero-, and Eastern Romance innovations (Lausberg 1971, Blasco Ferrer 1984).",
